article.title: Raytheon Awarded AIM 120D Software Test Integration Funds
article.author: George Seffers
article.text: Raytheon Company Missile Systems, Tucson, Arizona, is being awarded a $17,424,398 cost-plus-fixed-fee contract to provide test integration of software to enhance the system performance of the AIM- 120D missile.Â Air Armament Center, Eglin Air Force Base, Florida, is the contracting activity.
